CommonFields.Title: In situ polymerization and characterization of polyamide-6/silica nanocomposites derived from water glass
Author: Shen, Liang
Du, Qiangguo
Wang, Haitao
Zhong, Wei
Yang, Yuliang
CommonFields.Location: Department of Macromolecular Science, The Key Laboratory of Molecular Engineering of Polymers, Ministry of Education, People's Republic of China, and Fudan University, Shanghai 200433, People's Republic of China

FillerComponent.ManufacturerOrSourceName: Jiading Water Glass Factory, Shanghai, China

Mixing.Description: A water glass solution (3.2 mol l−1) was adjusted to pH 2.0 with an aqueous H2SO4 solution under ambient conditions.
The solution was saturated with NaCl and then an equal volume of THF was added.

ChooseParameter.Other: The mixture was stored at 10 ◦C for 30 min

Drying-Evaporation.Description: Separation of organic layer occurred and resultant was dried over 4 A molecular ˚ sieves

Mixing.Description: The monomers were stirred at rt until dissolved

ChooseParameter.Other: The mixture was then charged into a four-necked flask equipped with a mechanical stirrer, thermometer with temperature controller, nitrogen inlet and distillation facility.

Heating.Description: The mixture was heated until THF was completely removed through distillation.

ChooseParameter.Other: The ring-opening polymerization of ε-caprolactam went on for 5 hrs at 250 C under a stream of nitrogen.
The products were mechanically crushed and soaked in boiling water for 1 hr to extract unreacted monomer and oligomers

Scanning_Electron_Microscopy.EquipmentUsed: JSM-5600LV scanning electron microscope (JEOL Corporation, Japan)
